    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "5f31c9a9_a0b1d0d2",
        "filename": "cmd/dstool/main.go",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 202,
      "author": {
        "id": 5620
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-06-26T14:28:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We are enumerating keys and in this mode every key can have at most one parent. \nWe group the keys by that parent because updating/deleting keys with ancestors automatically are done in a transaction over the whole entity group.\nIf done differently we get contention issues. \nI might misunderstand the question.",
      "parentUuid": "e583493f_8f7a4cb0",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 202,
        "startChar": 38,
        "endLine": 202,
        "endChar": 51
      },
      "revId": "07cdc367152c8e6ee35d4ed8b0f75b09d93b3a49",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "80339956_2e4d459f",
        "filename": "cmd/dstool/main.go",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 202,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-06-26T14:51:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Suppose my entity group consists of three kinds: Grandparent, Parent, Child. Child\u0027s key.Parent points to Parent; Parent\u0027s key.Parent points to Grandparent. Grandparent is the root of the entity group. Will it cause problems to group Child entities for the same Parent, but process Child entities for the same Grandparent in separate transactions?",
      "parentUuid": "5f31c9a9_a0b1d0d2",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 202,
        "startChar": 38,
        "endLine": 202,
        "endChar": 51
      },
      "revId": "07cdc367152c8e6ee35d4ed8b0f75b09d93b3a49",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "612935b4_735df167",
        "filename": "cmd/dstool/main.go",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 232,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-06-22T13:57:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This potentially overwrites a non-empty procSlice if we have one or more with-parent keys followed by a no-parent key that causes byParent[0] to reach maxSliceSize.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 231,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 232,
        "endChar": 21
      },
      "revId": "07cdc367152c8e6ee35d4ed8b0f75b09d93b3a49",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ae7efb56_de7b9b78",
        "filename": "cmd/dstool/main.go",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 232,
      "author": {
        "id": 5620
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-06-26T14:28:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Done\nMade it mutually exclusive, in practice that\u0027s unlikely, because one Kind usually has or doesn\u0027t have a parent across all entities.",
      "parentUuid": "612935b4_735df167",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 231,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 232,
        "endChar": 21
      },
      "revId": "07cdc367152c8e6ee35d4ed8b0f75b09d93b3a49",
